Acceptable Use Policy
OneHost Cloud is providing You with access to certain OneHost Cloud Services (which may include software, networking, and other computing resources) (collectively, the “OneHost Cloud Hosting Services”) for Your lawful consumption and use in conformance with their intended use (as generally described on the relevant OneHost Cloud website associated with the particular OneHost Cloud Service). In connection with the OneHost Cloud Services, You and/or your users may provide or use “Content” (as defined in the Services Agreement) in connection with the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services. Your use of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services, including Content, is subject to the restrictions set forth in this Acceptable Use Policy, in addition to the terms of Your agreement with OneHost Cloud (Your “Services Agreement”). OneHost Cloud may change or modify this Acceptable Use Policy at any time and for any reason by posting a new version of this Policy at https://onehostcloud.hosting/legal/acceptable-use.php. You are responsible for monitoring this site and ensuring you are aware of the current terms. If you violate this Acceptable Use Policy, we may suspend or terminate your access to the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services. Set forth below are examples of prohibited conduct and Content in order to assist you in your use. Please note, however, that this list below is not exhaustive and you should follow the overriding principles contained in each section below.

No Illegal, Harmful or Obscene Content
Your use of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services is subject to all applicable laws and regulations, and you agree not to violate such laws and/or regulations. In addition, you agree not to post, distribute, promote, facilitate or transmit any of the following through use of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services:

Illegal Content including Content that incorporates gambling or child pornography.
Content that violates, misappropriates or infringes the third party intellectual property rights of others. ( DMCA Plan Exceptions and Bulletproof Hosting )
Content that solicits, encourages or promotes the use of illegal substances or activities.
Content that is threatening, abusive, harassing, defamatory, libelous, derogatory or violent.
Content that is invasive of a third party's legal rights (including privacy or publicity rights). ( DMCA Plan Exceptions and Bulletproof Hosting )
Content that is vulgar, obscene, bigoted or hateful or that advocates racial or ethnic intolerance.
Content that is profane, scandalous, pornographic, indecent or otherwise objectionable.
Content that is malicious or contains technology that may damage, interfere with, or intercept any system, program or data, including viruses, Trojan horses, worms, time bombs or other harmful or disruptive components.
No Illegal, Abusive or Harmful Actions
We are providing access to the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services for the purposes generally described on the OneHost Cloud website relevant to the specific OneHost Cloud Services and not for the purpose of interfering with other users' enjoyment or to harass third parties. For these reasons, you are prohibited from actions such as the following:

Using the OneHost Cloud Services or OneHost Cloud Hosting Services for any act or action that gives rise to civil or criminal liability for yourself or for OneHost Cloud or otherwise violates any applicable law.
Engaging in any activity that inappropriately restricts or inhibits any other user from using or enjoying the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services, including "hacking", "cracking", "spoofing", or defacing any portions of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services, including any OneHost Cloud websites.
Posting, distributing or transmitting chain letters, mass mailings, spam mail, any robot, spider, site search/retrieval application, or other manual or automatic device or process to retrieve, index or "data mine".
Harvesting or collecting information about OneHost Cloud Hosting Services users without their express written consent.
Interfering with others' enjoyment of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services, including intentionally attempting to overload any portion of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services.
Launching or facilitating a denial of service attack (DoS) from or on the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services.
Using the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services in connection with illegal or unlawful file sharing. ( DMCA Plan Exceptions and Bulletproof Hosting )
Using the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services to operate a general-purpose proxy or “open proxy” service.
Using the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services as a “miner” or “forger” of BitCoin or other cryptocurrencies.
While we strive to make our service as useful as possible, we don't support all workload profiles on the OneHost Cloud service. Distributed processing or other activities that continuously exhaust a specific resource (e.g. CPU, Network, Memory) are not allowed. Applications are allowed to consume available resources for a short period of time, but not continuously. If you have questions about your use case, feel free to contact us.

No Prohibited Access or Security Breaches
You may not use the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services in any manner that would compromise or violate the security of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services or other users of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services, including but not limited to engaging in any of the following:

Accessing or using the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services in violation of law, the terms of the Services Agreement or without permission, including attempting to test the vulnerability of the security of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services or to breach any of the security measures of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services.
Imitating or impersonating another person or his or her email address or creating false accounts intended to misrepresent yourself or the source of your email.
Intercepting or monitoring activity on the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services without permission.
Accessing any other host, user or network without permission.
Using any means to circumvent the security limitations of the OneHost Cloud Hosting Services.
Monitoring & Reporting
OneHost Cloud encourages you to report violations of this Acceptable Use Policy to OneHost Cloud immediately. OneHost Cloud has the right, but not the obligation, to monitor Your activity and Content to determine compliance with this Acceptable Use Policy. OneHost Cloud has the right in its sole discretion to edit, refuse to post or remove any material submitted to or posted on a OneHost Cloud website or other OneHost Cloud Hosting Services resource that we find to be in violation of this Acceptable Use Policy or is otherwise objectionable. You are solely responsible for Your activities and any Content you post, transmit or otherwise make available on a OneHost Cloud website or other OneHost Cloud Hosting Services resource. You acknowledge and agree that OneHost Cloud does not have any liability for any action or inaction with respect to Your conduct, communication or posting on a OneHost Cloud website or other OneHost Cloud Hosting Services resource.

Remote Security Testing
Remote security testing (aka penetration testing) is only allowed on our Pentesting VPS Hosting. Any users who use our normal Linux Cloud or Windows VPS for pentesting will have their services suspended or terminated.

Quota & Limits
The OneHost Cloud Hosting Services has certain soft and hard limits in using its service. Hard limits are automatically enforced by the Platform. Soft limits are consumable resources that you agree not to exceed.

Inode Limits: Plan Dependent - Hard
CPU Usage: 90% - Hard
Network Bandwidth: Plan Dependent - Soft
I/O Usage: 1Mbps 15mins - Hard
MySQL Use - Plan Dependent Hard
VPS Rebuilds: 3 per hour - Hard
Remote MySQL: 500GB - Month
OS Changes: 10 Per month - Hard
